<item>
            <title>[LU-8970] Kernel warning on client mount if pool is defined multiple times</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8970</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Steps to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;unmount the lustre FS completely (clients and all targets)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Mount just the MGS&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lctl pool_new (fsname).(poolname)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;repeat step 3&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Remount the FS.  Client will generate a kernel warning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This should also work on a filesystem with an MGS mounted on it&apos;s own node with no MDT or client.&lt;/p&gt;

